d 'PMEAN': module to compute panel-data means and exact within-between decomposition for two- and three-dimensional panel data
d
d      pmean computes panel-data means and the exact within-between
d decomposition for    two-dimensional (id x time) and
d three-dimensional (id x time x dim3) panel data. For each   
d input variable, the command generates marginal means (overall, by
d id, by time, and    optionally by a third dimension), the implied
d within and between components, and two- and	 three-way
d fixed-effect residuals.  With dim3() and full, the command
d additionally	  generates the full ANOVA-style pairwise
d interaction components and the three-way    residual.    The
d additive identities (2D, 3D main effects, and full 3-way ANOVA)
d hold exactly at every    observation in any panel, balanced or
d unbalanced. The third dimension can represent a    sector,
d region, product group, industry, cohort, or any other grouping
d observed alongside	the panel id and time.	  The estimation
d sample is defined by if, in, and observations with nonmissing
d values of    id(), time(), and, when supplied, dim3().  Missing
d values of the analysis variables are	  handled variable by
d variable unless the listwise option is specified. 
d
d KW: panel data
d KW: means
d KW: within
d KW: between
d
d Requires: Stata version 15.1 
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260519
d
d Author: Ahmad Nawaz,   Department of Economics, University of Sahiwal
d Support: email ahmadnawaz@@uosahiwal.edu.pk
